    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1956-07-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1956-07-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="684"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d684">
                <head>684. Telegram 72 to Geneva<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d684fn1">Source:
                        Department of State, Central Files, 611.93/7–2356. Secret. Drafted by
                            <persName corresp="#p_MWP_1">McConaughy</persName>. Pouched to Hong
                        Kong, London, and Taipei. The time of transmission is illegible.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1956-07-23">July 23, 1956</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <pb facs="d684-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d684-1"/>
                <p>72. Deptel 60.</p>
                <p>British Embassy July 20 transmitted to British Chargé O’Neill Peiping our request
                    that he renew immediately and insistently to Chinese Communist authorities
                    request that he be allowed to visit all American prisoners.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HH_1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Hoover</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
